@startuml

!theme plain
top to bottom direction
skinparam linetype ortho

interface Product {
  +name() : String
  +description() : String
  +price() : BigDecimal
  +type() : ProductType
}

entity BaseProduct << record >> {
  +product : common.Product
  +name() : String
  +description() : String
  +price() : BigDecimal
  +type() : ProductType
}

abstract class ProductDecorator {
  #product : Product
  +name() : String
  +description() : String
  +price() : BigDecimal
  +type() : ProductType
}

class Discounted {
  +price() : BigDecimal
  +description() : String
}
class Taxed {
  +price() : BigDecimal
  +description() : String
}
class GiftWrapped {
  +price() : BigDecimal
  +description() : String
}

note top of ProductDecorator
  Classic GoF Decorator: each decorator implements the
  same Product interface and wraps a Product, delegating
  the untouched parts and overriding price()/description().
  Decorators stack, so behaviour is added dynamically
  without touching the wrapped component.
end note

BaseProduct       .up.|>  Product
ProductDecorator  .up.|>  Product
Discounted        --up|>  ProductDecorator
Taxed             --up|>  ProductDecorator
GiftWrapped       --up|>  ProductDecorator
ProductDecorator  o-->  "1" Product : "wraps"
BaseProduct       -[#595959,dashed]->  Product : "adapts common.Product"
@enduml
